==Continuity==
''Splinter of the Mind's Eye'' was the first [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]] novel.<ref name="SWYouTube" />

The Kaiburr crystal that appears in ''Splinter of the Mind's Eye'' was based on<ref name="SW-CargoofDoom">{{SW|url=series/clone-wars/cargo-of-doom-trivia-gallery|text="Cargo of Doom" Trivia Gallery}} {{C|Image 2}}</ref> the "Kiber crystal," a Force-focusing artifact that appears in the [[Adventures of the Starkiller, Episode I: The Star Wars|second]] and [[The Star Wars: From The Adventures of Luke Starkiller|third]] drafts of the script for ''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope''.<ref name="AotS">''[[Adventures of the Starkiller, Episode I: The Star Wars]]''</ref><ref name="FAoLTS">''[[The Star Wars: From The Adventures of Luke Starkiller]]''</ref> In the current ''Star Wars'' [[canon]], [[kyber crystal]]s are the power source for [[lightsaber]]s.<ref name="Test of Strenth">{{TCW|A Test of Strength}}</ref>

The planet Mimban, which was created for ''Splinter of the Mind's Eye'', appears in the [[2018]] film ''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story]]''.<ref name="Solo">''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story]]''</ref> In the [[2020]] [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] [[The Rise of Kylo Ren 4|''The Rise of Kylo Ren'' 4]], by [[Charles Soule]], an artifact called the "[[Mindsplinter]]" is mentioned as being from the [[Minemoon]] of Mimban.<ref name="Rise of Kylo Ren">[[The Rise of Kylo Ren 4|''The Rise of Kylo Ren'' 4]]</ref>

==Legacy==
A four-issue ''Splinter of the Mind's Eye'' [[Star Wars: Splinter of the Mind's Eye (comic series)|comic-book adaptation]] was published by [[Dark Horse Comics]] in [[1995]].<ref name="DarkHorse">{{DarkHorse|url=Comics/93-816/Star-Wars-Splinter-of-the-Minds-Eye-1-of-4|text=Star Wars: Splinter of the Mind's Eye #1 (of 4)}}</ref> A music track titled "Splinter of the Mind's Eye" was composed by [[Jesse Harlin]] for the [[2019]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] expansion ''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic: Onslaught]]''.<ref name="TORYouTube">{{TORYouTube|video=fW1-CAtM7XM|text=Splinter Of The Minds Eye|date=2020-12-12}}</ref>

